# New concept: sandbox → practice lesson → Mongo → registries → visualization

Use this when a developer has iterated on a runnable under **`sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/`** and wants a full **TraceLab concept**: downloadable practice, editor **`codeFiles`**, optional **simulation**, and curriculum wiring. (**`topic`** here is the sandbox folder name; the catalog **slug** / URL may differ, e.g. **`load-balancing`**.)

Path examples: **`sandbox/system-design/load-balancer/`** (folder name is usually short; URL slug may differ, e.g. **`load-balancing`**).

---

## Files you will touch (every new concept)

This is the **complete list** of files that change for a typical new concept. Use it as a checklist:

| Area | File(s) | What you do |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **Sandbox** | `sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/go/`, `sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/python/`, `sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/typescript/` | Create one language folder per supported lab language; each folder includes `LAB.md`, starter, tests, and optional solution (§1). |
| **Practice → Mongo** | *(command only)* | Seed `practice.languages[]` (not only `practice.files`) using `sync-sandbox-practice` + a JSON spec (see §3A). |
| **Lesson panel** | `apps/web/src/components/lessons/<lab>/<Topic>Lesson.tsx` | New text-lesson component (`LessonRoot` / `LessonProblem` / `LessonDiagram` / `LessonTradeoffs`). |
| **Lesson registry** | `apps/web/src/features/curriculum/lesson-registry.ts` | Import + register `"<slug>": <Topic>Lesson`. |
| **Simulation** | `apps/web/src/components/simulations/<lab>/<Topic>Simulation.tsx` + `.module.css` | SVG sim matching the user's PNG; reuse `CachingSimulation.module.css` panel chrome; rAF packet animation; `onMetrics` emitting metric ids. |
| **Simulation registry** | `apps/web/src/lib/simulation-registry/` | Thin adapter (`VizComponent`) + `VIZ_REGISTRY['<vizType>']` in `index.ts`. |
| **Lesson page** | `apps/web/src/features/learning/pages/lesson-page.tsx` | Only if a new `practice.folder` fallback is needed in `resolveVizComponent`; otherwise **no change**. |
| **API** | `services/api/internal/catalog/handler.go` | Only if new `normalizeCodeFilesForLesson` edge cases appear; otherwise **no change**. |
| **SPA types** | `apps/web/src/types/lab-concept.ts` | Only if new fields are added to the lesson payload; otherwise **no change**. |
| **Code panel** | `apps/web/src/components/code/DynamicCodePanel.tsx` | Only if new lang/content fallback rules; otherwise **no change**. |
| **Mongo** | `Labs` doc (`topics[]` with `conceptSlugs`; no embedded `concepts[]`), `Concepts` doc (`_id`, `labId`, `topicId`, `slug`, vizType, codeFiles, parameters, metricGroups, practice) | Manual edits in Atlas (or **`mongodump`** / **`mongorestore`** to copy collections between DBs). |
| **Career tracks** | `services/api/internal/certifications/defaults.go` + Mongo `Certifications.track_tags` | Add concept-aligned tags to relevant tracks, then run **`make seed-certifications`** so Track filter includes the new concept when tags match. |
| **README** | `sandbox/README.md` | Document the new sandbox path if useful; practice sync stays generic (**`make sync-sandbox-mongo`**). |

Items marked **"no change"** are already generic enough from previous concepts. The first six rows are always new files or edits (practice sync is a command, not a new file).

---

## 1. Practice bundle (under `sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/`)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| **`go/main.go`** | Go starter (`TODO`s), solved by `go/main_test.go`. |
| **`go/main_test.go`** | Go canonical tests. |
| **`go/go.mod`** | Go module metadata. |
| **`python/main.py`** | Python starter (`TODO`s), solved by `python/test_main.py`. |
| **`python/test_main.py`** | Python canonical tests (`unittest`). |
| **`typescript/main.ts`** | TypeScript starter (`TODO`s), solved by `typescript/main.test.ts`. |
| **`typescript/main.test.ts`** | TypeScript canonical tests. |
| **`*/solution.*`** | Optional per-language reference solution matching starter API. |
| **`*/LAB.md`** | Per-language setup + run instructions. |

### Editor `codeFiles` vs ZIP

- **`Concepts` / `Labs`** **`codeFiles`** (Implementation panel) should expose **read-only teaching slices**: usually **`present.go`** and **`bad.go`** with optional **`role`**: `present` / `bad`.
- The working starter file lives in the selected language bundle under **`practice.languages[].files`** (legacy concepts may still use `practice.files` fallback), not merged into **`codeFiles`** for editing in the same way — see **`DynamicCodePanel`** + API **`normalizeCodeFilesForLesson`**.
- Practically: once **`main.go`** is stable as the student exercise, **copy/refine that logic into `present.go`** for the “good” reference; **`bad.go`** is a deliberate broken variant.

### `solution.go` and `main_test.go` (required invariant)

**`solution.go` must pass the lesson tests by construction:** if you take the solution body (everything that belongs in the student file — types, functions, **`main`** as needed) and **paste it into `main.go`** in place of the starter stubs, then **`go test ./...`** must pass. The reference implementation and **`main_test.go`** must stay in lockstep: same exported/unexported surface the tests exercise, no extra manual steps. Keep **`//go:build ignore`** on **`solution.go`** so the default package build stays the student **`main.go`**.

### HTTP / servers

Extract a **small testable API** into **`main.go`** / tests; keep servers or demos in **`present.go`** so **`go test ./...`** stays hermetic.

