## 2. `parameters` and `metricGroups` (Mongo / `LabConceptDetail`)

Define these on the merged lesson payload. **`Concepts`** (`_id`: `"<labId>/<slug>"`) is the source of truth for detail; if a legacy lab still has an embedded **`Labs.concepts[]`** row, **`Concepts`** wins on overlapping keys.

**`parameters`** drive **`ParametersPanel`** (`LabParameter` in **`apps/web/src/types/lab-concept.ts`**). Example pattern (caching-style):

```json
"parameters": [
  {
    "id": "hitRate",
    "type": "slider",
    "label": "HIT RATE",
    "min": 0,
    "max": 100,
    "unit": "%",
    "default": 70
  },
  {
    "id": "spawnRate",
    "type": "slider",
    "label": "SPAWN RATE",
    "min": 200,
    "max": 2000,
    "unit": "ms",
    "default": 900,
    "readOnly": true
  }
]
```

**`metricGroups`** drive **`MetricsPanel`**. Each **`metrics[].id`** must match **string keys** emitted by your simulation adapter’s **`onMetrics`** (see **`lib/simulation-registry/`**). Example (caching):

```json
"metricGroups": [
  {
    "label": "PERFORMANCE METRICS",
    "metrics": [
      { "id": "latency", "label": "LATENCY", "accent": true },
      { "id": "throughput", "label": "THROUGHPUT", "accent": true },
      { "id": "cacheHit", "label": "CACHE HIT", "accent": true },
      { "id": "successRate", "label": "SUCCESS RATE", "accent": true }
    ]
  },
  {
    "label": "REQUEST LOG",
    "metrics": [
      { "id": "hits", "label": "HITS", "color": "var(--accent)" },
      { "id": "misses", "label": "MISSES", "color": "var(--color-hard)" },
      { "id": "total", "label": "TOTAL" }
    ]
  }
]
```

For a **new** simulation, define **`metricGroups` last**, after you know the exact ids your component or adapter emits (or stub the viz first, then align Mongo).

