## Prompt snippet for the agent

> I have a working **`main.go`** under **`sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/`**. Here is a PNG of the architecture flow I want the simulation to match: *(attach PNG)*.
>
> 1. Turn the sandbox into a **practice bundle**: **`go.mod`**, **`main.go`** (student starter with TODOs), **`main_test.go`**, **`solution.go`** (`//go:build ignore` — must pass `go test` when pasted into `main.go`), **`present.go`** (idiomatic demo), **`bad.go`** (anti-pattern), **`LAB.md`**.
> 2. Wire **`sync-sandbox-practice`** for **`Concepts._id` `<labId>/<slug>`**.
> 3. Define **`parameters`** and **`metricGroups`** for the simulation. Metric ids must match what the viz component emits via **`onMetrics`**.
> 4. Build the **SVG simulation** matching the attached PNG — nodes, edges, animated request packets — inside the **Architecture Visualizer** panel header. Register it in **`lib/simulation-registry/`** under **`vizType` `<key>`**.
> 5. Register the **text lesson** panel in **`features/curriculum/lesson-registry.ts`** (slug **`<slug>`**).

Adjust **`<lab>`**, **`<topic>`**, **`<labId>/<slug>`**, **`vizType`**, and sim vs text-only.
